                    "company": "UWB",
                    "description": "I conduct a research on the transformation of the Brabandic countryside of the Netherlands in the Late Middle Ages and Early Modern Period. During this period we see considerable changes occurring in almost all social field. Most notable are the rise of the central authority of the Duke of Brabant and the formation of an administrative infrastructure, changing property relations, the rise of cities and markets and the construction of monumental churches. However, archaeological observations show that also on a local scale profound developments took place like the relocation of settlements, changes in farming practice and house building and changes in agricultural stratigies and land ownership. \nThis study aims to examine these various developments in the rural landscape and explore how they wee mutually related and how they were related to wider political, economic and administrative developments.",
                    "title": "Phd-onderzoeker",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
        },
